news.title: China Evergrande liquidation hearing in Hong Kong court adjourned to January
news.para: The hearing into the petition was adjourned to Jan. 29, the court said in an unexpected move on Monday, after Evergrande's lawyers sought an adjournment, saying no creditors were "actively seeking" liquidation.

news.title: Pune: 30 properties get notices for encroachments in green belt
news.para: These properties have been established by flouting the green belt norms, wherein construction of commercial or residential nature is not allowed.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: Prefabricated facility of 50,000 sq ft to come up at Technopark P1
news.para: ​"The tender is set to be issued soon. Prefab is a good concept for parking companies and they can be shifted to available built up spaces at any given point of time. The concept also saves time and could reduce the load on the queue system," said Col Sanjeev Nair (Retd), the chief executive officer Park Centre, Technopark.

news.title: Over 1,200 buildings unsafe in Nagpur, occupants told to vacate premises
news.para: The department has declared 1,286 of them as unsafe and served notices to occupants to vacate the buildings, said a senior fire department official.

news.title: Ericsson in talks to pick up over five lakh sq ft workspace on lease from Skootr in Gurugram
news.para: The company has signed an agreement to lease about 325,000 sq ft for immediate move-in and kept the right of first refusal for another 200,000 sq ft.

news.title: About 5,000 registries across 20 projects in past four months: Greater Noida development body
news.para: GNIDA CEO Ravi Kumar NG said that the registries generated a revenue of Rs 100 crore, while the stamp duty payments from those transactions amounted to Rs 150 crore for the state government.

news.title: China Evergrande risking liquidation if creditors veto its plan for handling huge debts
news.para: Last month, the company said Chinese police were investigating Evergrande's chairman, Hui Ka Yan, for unspecified suspected crimes in the latest obstacle to the company's efforts to resolve its financial woes.

news.title: Property tax will not be collected from rural residential areas: Delhi Mayor
news.para: “MCD will not collect property tax from any rural residential areas in Delhi from now on. During the 15 years of BJP’s administration in MCD, people were greatly troubled by notices for property tax being sent," said mayor Shelly Oberoi.

news.title: Gujarat HC orders Gulab Tower residents to pay Rs 79 crore till December 31 or vacate plot
news.para: AMC valued Final Plot 100/E at Rs 79 crore at the rate of Rs 1.70 lakh per metre and asked Snehanjali Society to pay for it. Snehanjali Society’s land on Final Plot 65 was valued at Rs 1.38 lakh per square metre.

news.title: MCD to rent out its office building complex in East Delhi's Karkardooma
news.para: The state-of-the-art office complex, located in the Karkardooma Institutional area, comprises three blocks -- A, B, and C -- and is constructed over 22,918 sq metre. All three blocks are ready to be leased out by the corporation, the statement said.

news.title: Bidhannagar Police seek info on PGs from New Town RWAs
news.para: They plan to make a database of outsiders staying as paying guests in the complexes. The cops are also asking owners to maintain a list of documents from the paying guests and provide them if necessary.

news.title: Cash-strapped Ludhiana civic body launches drive to recover pending rent
news.para: Officials said that they would seal shops if defaulters did not clear their dues. This year, the income target from rental properties is around Rs 10 crore and not much has been recovered so far.

news.title: Odisha government aims to resolve land disputes and issue record of rights
news.para: Officials have been directed to promptly resolve the disputes and expedite the issuance of RoRs. Grievances related to land disputes and RoR acquisition had been received, prompting the government's proactive measures.

news.title: Jharkhand housing board plans to take legal steps against 500 violators
news.para: Speaking to TOI on Saturday, JSHB chairman Sanjay Lal Paswan said they have issued notices to over 500 identified defaulters.

news.title: Pune civic body seeks fire audits at malls, commercial firms
news.para: “The administration has issued directives to shopping malls. They have been told to take precautions against fire safety. We have a system in place for checking if these facilities are in place or not,” said Devendra Potphode, head of the PMC’s fire brigade department.

news.title: Swedish property firms should cut debt, raise equity: Riksbank Governor
news.para: Commercial property companies ramped up borrowing when rates were low and some are now struggling to pay off or roll-over debt after eight interest rate hikes by the central bank.

news.title: China's Logan Group seeks to postpone Dec 4 liquidation hearing: State media
news.para: The Shenzhen-based company said last year it would suspend interest payments and restructure its offshore debt including $3.7 billion in dollar bonds due to liquidity pressure.
